# Standing instructions for Rob's projects

These are corrections I've had to give Cursor repeatedly. Follow them by default.

## Numbers are sacred

Never substitute a number you "think is more common". Grep
`scripts/launchlook_constants.py` (or the project's equivalent) before
changing any count. Current canonical values:

- Free trial: **2 findings**
- Starter Package ($19): **10 findings**
- Scale Up Package ($49): **30 findings**
- Pro Package ($99): **40 findings**

If you change a number, update every call site and the drift test in `tests/`.

## Brand voice

- ❌ "Trust Gaps", "synergize", "leverage" → ✅ "embarrassing bugs", plain English
- ❌ "native apps" → ✅ "desktop and mobile width testing"
- ❌ em-dashes in customer-facing copy → ✅ commas, periods, or rephrase
- Voice is informal and human; Rob will ship with light edits, not a rewrite

## UI defaults

- Status messages, disclaimers, and microcopy under primary CTAs: **`text-center`**
- Footer is Rob's personal contact card (name, 1-line bio, email, LinkedIn) — never a corporate footer
- URL inputs accept bare hostnames (`mysite.com`); normalize client AND server side

## Workflow preferences

- **Clickable links in emails, not CLI commands.** If you find yourself writing "run `python ...`" in a notification, ask if it can be a link to the local Flask UI instead.
- **Don't create new docs/markdown files proactively.** Update `docs/ROB-REMAINING-TODO.md` and the project snapshot canvas; ask before creating anything else.
- Commit messages: one line, present tense, scoped (`fix(audit): ...`, `landing: ...`). No multi-line bodies for small changes.

## Before pushing

```
python -m ruff check <changed-files>
python -m ruff format <changed-files>
python -m pytest tests/ -x -q
```

All three green or don't push. Pass specific paths to `ruff format`, never the whole repo.

## Shell is PowerShell

- ❌ `cmd1 && cmd2` → ✅ `cmd1; if ($?) { cmd2 }`
- ❌ heredocs (`<<EOF`) → ✅ here-strings (`@"..."@`) or `git commit -F file`
- Set `$env:PYTHONIOENCODING="utf-8"` before scripts that print Unicode
- PowerShell wraps stderr in `NativeCommandError` even on exit 0 — read actual output before assuming failure

## Email notifications

- Always send **multipart HTML + text** via Resend (`html` + `text` fields)
- Set explicit `User-Agent` on every outbound HTTP call (Cloudflare WAF blocks `Python-urllib/X.Y`)
- Long mailto URLs go inside `<a href>` tags only — never in plain-text bodies

## LLM prompts for tiered products

Use **target ranges with explicit minimums**, never just "up to N". Pair with
an anti-padding guardrail: "You may NOT invent findings to pad the count. If
a category truly does not apply, skip it."

## Vercel Python serverless

`api/*.py` must be self-contained. Don't import from `scripts/` — inline
constants and add a drift test in `tests/` instead. `FUNCTION_INVOCATION_FAILED`
at cold start means a top-level import didn't bundle.

## Notion property values

Normalize at the boundary (`TIER_NORMALIZE` lowercase dict). Log a WARN when
an unrecognised value falls through to the default — silent fallbacks (`.get(k, 7)`)
hide bugs for weeks.

